# 8. Functional Requirements

## FR-001: Job Collection

The system shall:

* Execute on a scheduled basis every four hours.
* Retrieve jobs from approved public sources.
* Retrieve complete job descriptions whenever available.
* Capture metadata associated with each posting.

---

## FR-002: Job Normalization

The system shall normalize all job postings into the following structure:

* Title
* Company
* Location
* Salary
* Description
* Source
* URL
* Date Posted
* Date Found

All downstream processing shall operate exclusively on this normalized structure.

---

## FR-003: Deduplication

The system shall generate a fingerprint using:

* Company
* Job Title
* Location

Hash generation:

MD5(
lower(company) +
lower(title) +
lower(location)
)

If the fingerprint already exists, the job shall not be inserted.

---

## FR-004: Job Persistence

The system shall persist:

* Original job information
* AI evaluations
* Application status
* User notes
* Timestamps

All information shall remain available for future review and analysis.

---

## FR-005: AI Evaluation

The system shall evaluate jobs using complete job descriptions and user preference data.

The AI evaluation shall return:

* Match Score (0-100)
* Recommendation
* Reasons
* Red Flags
* Role Categories
* AI Summary

Valid recommendations:

* Apply
* Review
* Ignore

---

## FR-006: Immediate Notifications

The system shall send Telegram notifications when:

Match Score >= 90

Notifications shall include:

* Job Title
* Company
* Location
* Match Score
* Recommendation
* Reasons
* Red Flags
* Job URL

---

## FR-007: Daily Digest

The system shall generate a daily digest containing:

80 <= Match Score < 90

The digest shall include:

* Total jobs identified
* Number of recommended opportunities
* Summary information for each recommended position

---

## FR-008: Application Tracking

The system shall support the following statuses:

* New
* Saved
* Applied
* Interviewing
* Rejected
* Closed
* Ignored

Status changes shall persist within the database.

